There are 2 external tools to setup - jshon and jansson.

For installation define the location AE_EXTERNALS to point at where you want
jshon and jansson to reside.  Morgan for example likes to build third party
tools in the directory /home/morgan/eval and so he will define:

    $ export AE_EXT=/home/morgan/eval

IMPORTANT: This process assumes "crusty" has already been downloaded and
           that $AE_EXT/crusty where is resides.  If "crusty" resides
           somewhere else, just link it in:

    $ ln -s /home/morgan/some/where/else/crusty $AE_EXT/crusty

jansson
-------

    $ cd $AE_EXT
    $ curl http://www.digip.org/jansson/releases/jansson-2.3.1.tar.gz | \
    > tar zxf -
    $ ln -s jansson* jansson
    $ cd jansson
    $ ./configure
    $ make

jshon
-----

    $ cd $AE_EXT
    $ curl http://kmkeen.com/jshon/jshon.tar.gz | \
    > tar zxf -
    $ cd jshon
    $ export C_INCLUDE_PATH=$AE_EXT/jansson/src
    $ export LIBRARY_PATH=$AE_EXT/jansson/src/.libs
    $ make




export DYLD_LIBRARY_PATH=$AE_EXT/jansson/src/.libs
export LD_LIBRARY_PATH=$AE_EXT/jansson/src/.libs






